reviews.review_text:
bread crumb This is Brent's first Casey Jones, a song that he would play only 18 times. Considering that the band played it what seemed like every night from mid '69 to '73, that's amazingly rare.  I'm going to guess that like everyone else in the mid '80s, they figured out that cocaine was not all it was cracked up to be ;)  

I think what is remarkable about this show is that there is nothing all that remarkable about the set list - it's just well-played from start to finish, reflective of a very strong few years before the smack got in the way.
